race.description: Performance Access Resources Provincial Mdn Hcp
race.comment: BRAINIAC (9) returned last start and worked home nicely to get up for third over this distance at Bathurst. That was her best figure in four career runs so she has returned better than ever. Nicely placed to go on and break the maiden. HERAION (6) stoked up late but just missed last time out over this course and distance. Has taken a long while to hit her straps but that last run suggests she won't be a maiden for long. BRUTAL ADVANCE (1) started favourite but had too much to do last time at Queanbeyan when beaten a half-length over 1000m. The extra 100m can only help. Serious contender. IMA CAPRI (7) was six weeks between runs when a close fifth in a similar race to this here 16 days ago. Very fit and from a good gate can play a big role. STRASSMAN (2) trialled well recently and cannot be ruled out first-up from a 158-day spell.
